</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1394,1635]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,491,1394,1419]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
. Benthopelagic species at depths ranging from 
<quantity box="[1024,1196,1395,1419]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6199999999999999" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="0.44" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" unit="m" value="1620.0" valueMax="2800.0" valueMin="440.0">440 to 2,800 m</quantity>
, but usually less than 
<quantity box="[151,224,1431,1455]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
(D'Onghia 
<emphasis box="[358,408,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. 2004). Present on both sides of the Atlantic and in the Mediterranean Sea. Occurs in the eastern Atlantic in the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[507,589,1466,1491]" name="Ireland" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Ireland</collectingCountry>
, Gulf of Biscay, 
<collectingCountry box="[781,848,1466,1491]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[860,958,1466,1491]" name="Portugal" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[969,1065,1466,1491]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Madeira</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1077,1159,1467,1491]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Azores</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1387,1466,1491]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
and the western African coast from 
<collectingCountry box="[504,605,1503,1526]" name="Morocco" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Morocco</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[640,785,1502,1527]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">
<collectingRegion box="[640,706,1502,1527]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Unguja" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">South</collectingRegion>
Africa
</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Quero" box="[799,1000,1502,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="Quero J. C., du Buit, M. H., Fonteneau, J., Laborde, J., Morandeau, L. G. &amp; Vayne, J. J. (1994) Observations Ichtyologiques effectuees en 1993. Annales de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles de la Charente-Maritime, 8, 359 - 369." type="journal article" year="1994">
Quéro 
<emphasis box="[877,926,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sulak" box="[1011,1140,1502,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="Sulak, K. J. (1990) Halosauridae. In: Quero, J. C. Hureau, J. C., Karrer, C. Post, A. &amp; Saldanha, L. (Eds.), Check-list of the fishes of the eastern tropical Atlantic (CLOFETA), UNESCO, JNICT &amp; SEI, Lisboa, Paris, pp. 126 - 132." type="book chapter" year="1990">Sulak 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Banon" box="[1152,1352,1502,1527]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="Banon, R., Casas, J. M., Pineiro, C. G. &amp; Covelo, M. (1997) Capturas de peces de afinidades tropicales en aguas atlanticas de Galicia (NO de la peninsula Iberica) Boletin del Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia, 13, 57 - 66." type="journal article" year="1997">
Bañón 
<emphasis box="[1232,1280,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. 1997
</bibRefCitation>
) and in the western Atlantic from 
<collectingRegion box="[464,584,1538,1563]" country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">
New 
<collectingRegion box="[529,584,1538,1563]" country="United Kingdom" name="York" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">York</collectingRegion>
</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[629,742,1538,1563]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, including the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1108,1538,1563]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">
<collectingRegion box="[1020,1108,1538,1563]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">Mexico</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
, the Caribbean Sea and the Antilles (
<bibRefCitation author="McEachran" box="[263,634,1574,1599]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="McEachran, J. D. &amp; Fechhelm, J. D. (1998) Fishes of the Gulf of Mexico. Vol. 1. Myxiniformes to Gasterosteiformes. University of Texas Press, Austin, 1120 pp." type="book" year="1998">McEachran &amp; Fechhelm 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Saavedra-Diaz" box="[656,979,1574,1599]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="Saavedra-Diaz, L. M., Roa-Varon, A., Acero-P., A. &amp; Mejia, L. S. (2004) Nuevos registros icticos en el talud superior del Caribe colombiano (Ordenes Albuliformes, Anguilliformes, Osmeriformes, Stomiiformes, Ateleopodiformes, Aulopiformes y Pleuronecetiformes). Boletin de investigaciones marinas y costeras, 33, 181 - 207." type="journal article" year="2004">
Saavedra-Díaz 
<emphasis box="[837,895,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
); only a few records in the western Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Pais" box="[376,555,1610,1635]" pageId="7" pageNumber="478" refString="Pais, A., Merella, P., Follesa, M. C. &amp; Motomura, H. (2009) North-easternmost record of Halosaurus ovenii (Actinopterygii: Notacanthiformes: Halosauridae) in the Mediterranean Sea, with notes on its biology. Acta Ichthyologica Et Piscatoria, 39, 33 - 37. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2009.39.1.06" type="journal article" year="2009">
Pais 
<emphasis box="[431,481,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="478">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
